title: Paid content for @CostaSunglasses

author: National Geographic
description:
Space Station
Breathtaking engineering triumphs hidden inside the International Space Station make it the most innovative and expensive superstructure ever built. 

Ultimate Cargo Ship
We take apart the GPO Amethyst, an ocean transporter capable of carrying some of the largest structures by deliberately sinking into the ocean. 

Monster Plane
This episode uncovers the innovations that enable the world’s largest plane, the unique Antonov AN-255, to carry the world’s heaviest air freight. 

Tallest Building
This episode reveals the incredible engineering behind the Burj Khalifa. At more than half a mile high, it’s the tallest skyscraper ever built. 

Giant Car Plant
Germany’s Wolfsburg car factory is the largest in the world. This episode uncovers the engineering and production innovations hidden inside it.    

Biggest Dome
The engineering behind the Singapore National Stadium, the stadium that holds the record for the largest free-spanning dome in the world, is revealed. 

Superstruct
title: Superstructures: Largest Structures in the World | MEGA EPISODE | National Geographic
